&lt;p&gt;Below is an animation for the short-time evolution of rogue wave of infinite order $\Psi(X,T)$, a special solution of the focusing NLS equation
&lt;/p&gt;
$$
\mathrm{i}\Psi_t + \frac{1}{2}\Psi_{XX}+|\Psi|^2\Psi=0,
$$
&lt;p&gt;
identified in this work. The computational method developed in this work is based on numerical solution of the Riemann-Hilbert problem representation of $\Psi(X,T)$ for each $(X,T)$. While this Mathematica module can be used in code repository linked above, we recommend using the more recent Julia software package &lt;a href=&#34;http://localhost:1313/publication/rwionls-jl/&#34;&gt;RogueWaveInfiniteNLS.jl&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
